cluster_relations.rel_desc: Ethical dilemmas in AI development are said to arise from concerns that include accountability.

qualifiers.OperationalConstraint: in the development and deployment of AI technologies
qualifiers.OtherQualifier: ConcernType: listed as one of multiple sources of dilemmas

cluster_relations.rel_desc: The document section titled "Ethical Dilemmas in AI Development" is a discussion of ethical dilemmas in AI development as a concept.
The ethical dilemma of transparency is specifically situated within AI development and, by extension, AI systems.
cluster_relations.subject_entity_name: ethical dilemma of transparency in AI
remarks: AI development is not an explicit entity; AI systems used as proxy for development context.

cluster_relations.rel_desc: Ethical dilemmas in AI development involve issues related to accountability.

qualifiers.OtherQualifier: IssueCategory: part of the multifaceted nature of ethical dilemmas

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that a broader ethical dilemma includes a specific concern or issue (e.g., accountability) as one of its components.
args.justification: Both relations link the same ethical dilemma concept in AI development to 'accountability' as an included concern/issue; a normalized predicate clarifies that accountability is a constituent concern of the dilemma rather than just a loose association.
args.remark: Used for relations where an ethical dilemma concept includes specific issues like accountability, privacy, bias, etc.

args.justification: These relations represent the inclusion of specific issues (accountability) within a broader ethical dilemma in AI development, forming a consistent class of 'dilemma ↔ constituent ethical issue' links.

The link is a conceptual/thematic inclusion of one concern within a broader dilemma, not causal, spatial, temporal, or compositional in a physical sense; it best fits a broad associative/thematic grouping.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that a document or document segment has a particular concept as its primary topic or subject matter.
args.justification: The relation explicitly states that the document section 'Ethical Dilemmas in AI Development' discusses the concept 'ethical dilemmas in AI development'; this is a standard document-to-topic aboutness relation.
args.remark: Use this predicate for document or section nodes pointing to their main conceptual topics.

args.justification: This relation links a document section to the concept it discusses, a canonical example of a document-to-topic relation class.
The semantics are strictly about what the document section is about, fitting a broad ABOUTNESS group rather than generic association.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that an ethical issue or dilemma is about or pertains to a particular system, domain, or context.
args.justification: The relation connects the 'ethical dilemma of transparency in AI' to 'AI systems' and describes the dilemma as being situated within AI systems; this is a conceptual 'dilemma concerns domain' predicate rather than a document-topic link.
args.remark: Use when an ethical issue or principle is described as pertaining to a specific type of AI system or technological context.

args.justification: The relation defines the scope or domain (AI systems) to which an ethical dilemma (transparency in AI) applies, forming a class of links that map ethical issues to their affected system/domain.
The dilemma is about or pertains to AI systems as its domain of application; this fits the broad ABOUTNESS dimension better than causality, composition, or spatiality.
args.remark: Borderline between ABOUTNESS and ASSOCIATION; chosen as ABOUTNESS to parallel document-topic style but for concept-to-domain links.
